## <a id='overview'></a>Overview

 <%= vars.product_short %> enables operators
to provide app developers with access to services through the `cf marketplace`.
These services run on Enterprise Pivotal Container Service (Enterprise PKS)
for consumption by <%= vars.pas_full %> apps.

For more information about the `cf marketplace`,
see [<%= vars.platform_name %> Developer Guide](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-5/devguide/index.html).
For more information about Enterprise PKS,
see [Enterprise Pivotal Container Service (PKS)](https://pivotal.io/platform/pivotal-container-service).

<%= vars.product_short %> enables platform operators to do the following:

* Offer ISV and open source Helm charts as on-demand services to <%= vars.pas_full %> developers.

<%= vars.product_short %> enables app developers to do the following:

* Provision dedicated service instances onto a Kubernetes cluster through the `cf marketplace`.
* Consume services running on Enterprise PKS in apps running on <%= vars.pas_full %>.

## <a id='features'></a> Key Features

<%= vars.product_short %> includes the following key features:

* A service broker that provisions dedicated service instances into a
Kubernetes cluster and binds service instances to PAS apps.
* A CLI for managing service offerings.
* The ability to create and manage a catalog of services to the `cf marketplace`.

